How to Navigate the Dashboard

· Sidebar (left) – main navigation: Home, Deployments, Environments, Tickets, User Profile.
· Dashboard Home – four cards link directly to each tool.
· Header – search (click or press /), notifications, help, user avatar – all show informative toasts.

---

What You Can Explore

1. Deployments Page

· Active deployment hero – live progress bar, current step, duration.
· Deployment Information – ID, status, commit, branch, triggered by, started at.
· Orange links – environment, pipeline, company, website (click to see toast).
· Action selector – choose Redeploy, Rollback, Cancel, or Restart, then click Submit.
· Deployments Tasks tab – lists all tasks; the currently running task appears at the top.
· Pipeline Configuration tab – read‑only pipeline steps, YAML preview, environment variables, artifacts.

2. Environments Page

· Status overview – four cards: Environment Health, Active Deployment, Issues Detected, Resource Summary (CPU/Memory).
· System insights – real‑time alerts (e.g., node memory critical, slow deployment).
· Tabs – General, Pods, Nodes, Deployments, Pipelines, Emails, Cache Warmer, Actions, Diagnostics, Autoscaler, Monitors, Quick Actions, Firewall.
· Deployments tab – create a new deployment via cascading dropdowns (account connection → provider → repository → branch → pipeline).
· Firewall tab – add/edit IP rules with IPv4 validation.

3. User Profile Page

· Profile Information – editable name, email, role, company, website (orange link).
· Change password modal (with validation).
· IP Whitelist – add/edit/delete, protected system rows, IPv4 validation.
· SSH Keys – add/edit/delete, fingerprint and last used shown.
· SSO – “Connect SSO” button (toast for future implementation).
· API Tokens – generate with scopes, one‑time token display with copy, revoke.
· Two‑Factor Authentication – enable/disable mock with QR code and 6‑digit verification.
· Notification Preferences – toggles for deployment, security, billing, product announcements (saved in localStorage).

4. Support Tickets Page

· Listing table – filter by status, search by ID/subject, sort by any column, pagination (5 per page).
· Click any ticket row – opens side panel with three tabs:
  · Comments – two distinct ways to add a comment: “Comment” (visible to customer) and “Send Reply” (staff only).
  · History – chronological timeline of status, priority, and assignment changes.
  · Details – ticket metadata plus company, agency, website as orange links.

5. Dashboard Home

· Central hub with cards linking to the four main tools.

---

Additional UX Highlights

· All interactive elements show toast notifications for feedback.
· Real‑time simulation – deployment progress updates every second, tasks appear dynamically.
· Responsive design – works on desktop, tablet, and mobile.
· Sidebar collapse – remembers your preference (localStorage).
· Empty states – tables with no data show helpful illustrations and messages.

---

